		<div class="col-6 text-start">
			<span>
				If your beloved canine companion frequently showers you with affectionate licks,
				you'll undoubtedly become intimately acquainted with the sensation of moist
				slobber adorning your visage, enveloping your hands, and encircling your mouth.
				Whether you find yourself engaged in a gentle petting session, nourishing your 
				faithful companion with nourishment, or receiving an exuberant welcome as you cross
				the threshold of your abode, the art of being licked by your furry friend becomes an 
				integral part of your daily routine. The act of receiving these moist expressions of 
				love from your dog serves as a heartwarming gesture of fondness, yet it harbors a myriad
				of intricate interpretations and significances beyond its apparent display of affection.
			</span>
